{
  "stem": "1799.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 849.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By that time, you know, as far as offense to the senses, you know, I was pretty numb.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And while I felt bad, the fact that I was alive, that I was given food-- by that time we were, by the way, moved from Auschwitz to Birkenau, which was a few miles away.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Auschwitz, I was only there maybe three or four days.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Birkenau is where I ended up in a barracks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was pretty sizable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was told even then, that at one time these barracks were used by horses.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had these large stables that were used by the Poles.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Birkenau and Auschwitz actually is today in Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And prior to the Second World War, it was Polish as well.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the Poles are known to be good with horses.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Anyway, we knew things were going on there that were different from other camps.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "First of all, it was very large.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was huge.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There must have been-- oh, just guessing, I couldn't see all the people-- but there were barracks, upon barracks, upon barracks.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a field of large barracks, where thousands of people were.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it wasn't until after I left Auschwitz and Birkenau, that I realized personally what else was happening there in connection with the burning and the gassing.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I didn't know that at the time I was there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All I know-- all I knew at the time is there were piles of clothing near where we were that were organized by some of the camp inmates as to what valuables they may have contained.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't know whose clothing they were.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It turned out later that they were clothing from people who were asked to go take a shower.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
